I decided to get off the No. 1 subway train at 125th and Broadway and after descending the escalator to the street level (at Broadway and Tiemann Place), the first thing I noticed was a modern Starbucks on the corner. Upon entering, I observed its spacious square design and saw that it was not crowded. I was able to place my order within 30 seconds and then I sat down in one of the four comfortable cushioned seats in a corner with the sunshine streaming through the large plate-glass windows.  This place looks like a good addition to this area and afterwards I plan to walk several blocks south to visit Grants Tomb on Riverside Drive. But I will say that despite the pleasant modern decor, the music, while not at the highest level, is a distraction and not to my liking.  I have encountered this sound annoyance problem at another Starbucks in Manhattan, at 92nd Street and Broadway, where the music (or noise) was so loud you could not talk on your telephone or to anyone because it seemed to he at an excruciatingly high volume.
